11/03/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian customs authorities announced Sunday (March 11th) that they have blocked an attempt to smuggle 163,402kg of heroin, with an estimated market value of 15m euros.
The drugs, found in a truck with a Turkish registration plate, were seized at the Kalotina border crossing.
This is the second biggest heroin confiscation in Bulgaria in five years, following the record 230kg seized at the Kapitan Andreevo border crossing in 2002.(Darik, BNR - 11/03/07)
